Install Photocatalog in 3 easy steps.  Lines beginning with $ are
commands to run as a local user and lines beginning with # are run as
root.

1.  Run the installer.  Add -f to install.pl to overwrite existing
configuration files.

	$ ./install.pl

2.  Setup Crontab based on example crontab created by installer.

	$ crontab -e

3.  (optional) Setup email alias in /etc/mail/aliases.

	Copy the example alias from example aliases to the system
	aliases file.
	# newaliases

See README for more information.
